      "content": "i see. so if originalism is about being \"objective\" and using history, does that mean other ways of interpreting the constitution—like living constitutionalism—are basically seen by experts as just being \"subjective\" or \"unscientific\"? or is there a legitimate scholarly reason to say the text should evolve with society?",
